The paper proposes a novel architecture for group activity recognition using deep learning techniques. The focus is on computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of LSTM networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of adversarial training, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (IR) tasks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
